RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 67. Claiming Purse 23232. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 20, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs . Claiming Price $20,000 (Races Where Entered For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ADD IT ALL UP was allowed to settle three wide through early stages, roused five wide into the lane, rallied along the outside, dug in gamely and edged away late. IVY ABAD GIRL tracked the top duo entering the turn, hustled along four wide into upper stretch, dug in gamely, took a slim lead then got outkicked by the winner in final stages. CENTERFOLD vied outside of rival entering the turn, continued to battle for the lead a furlong out then ultimately gave way. BARBED WIRE was unhurried through the early going, saved ground along the rail around the turn, cut the corner entering the lane and lacked a needed rally. SHELBY TO was not too far back in leaving the backstretch, swung four wide into the lane and never threatened. REMITTANCE SENT dueled inside of CENTERFOLD up the backstretch, battled on around the turn then tired in the lane.

GINGER RULES was unhurried in the back, cut the corner entering the lane and lacked a rally. TAKE ME UP BRADY raced up close two to three wide in early stages, continued in contention around the turn then tired in the drive. KWAI CHANG raced three to four wide in contention then came up empty in the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CRIMSON ZIP pressed the pace in opening stages, vied for command two wide around the turn, roused for more at the head of the lane, responded, edged ahead past the furlong marker and held late. SECRET BLARNEY settled off the pace in early stages, swung five wide into the lane, gathered strong momentum under a drive and finished lgamely. DISCREET INVASION raced in the back, saved ground the turn, cut the corner then angled two wide and advanced to capture show. COCO BRAVADO vied inside of a duo in opening stages, battled on holding a slim lead around the turn, cut the corner entering the lane, lost command shortly past the furlong marker and got edged for show. GOOD ONE settled off the early pace, swung five wide into the lane and failed to rally. COLD SNACK THIRTY came away last at the start and raced off the embattled leaders, advanced into contention four wide around the turn, failed to sustain bid in the lane and steadily weakened. FLY FIRST CLASS vied three deep for the lead in opening stages, battled on around the turn then tired in the drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 5 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHOULDABOUGHTDABAR set a pressured pace through the backstretch, edged ahead to a clearer lead around the far turn, continued to lead the way in the final furlong, got confronted by IMPECCABILITY in final stages, fought back gamely and prevailed. IMPECCABILITY was reserved racing in the back, continued well off the pace around the far turn, saved ground entering the lane, advanced into contention then switched to the outside of the leader, reached equal terms in final strides, dug in and just missed. RUNNINGFORCASH pressed the pace along the outside through early stages, continued in pursuit of the leader around the far turn, was no late match for the top pair but finished well clear for a share. RUDIANO rated off the early pace, hustled along four wide around the far turn, stayed in the same path into the lane and lacked a rally. UXMAL pressed the pace up the backstretch, began to flatten around the far turn then faded through the lane. GRAPHENE CASSOCK raced in range tracking the early leaders, failed to advance under pressure around the final turn and retreated in the lane. PRINCE OF EARL raced three to four wide and had no response.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNCASHED raced on top under some pressure in opening stages then edged away to a clear advantage, continued on top still unasked around the turn, saved ground entering the lane, was ridden out briefly in the upper stretch then settled in hand and geared down late. OCEAN OF STORMS was allowed to settle off the early pace, hustled up three to four wide entering the lane, was no match for the pulling away winner but produced a solid finish. KYANDI sat off the pace in early stages, swung four wide into the lane, sustained a steady bid and cleared the rest for a share. ARIZONA ANDREW was forwardly placed up the backstretch, began to flatten out around the turn and faded in the lane. CALL ME ICE MAN was forwardly placed while the closest pursuer of the early leader, sustained bid for the eventual winner around the turn then tired in the drive.
